                                "titre": "I used a scrap piece of 16 gauge steel that formed a long, narrow right triangle. I needed to convert it to an isosceles triangle. I drew a centerline from the point of the right triangle to the base line of it. I used a square to draw a new baseline perpendicular to the centerline and trimmed the right triangle to make it an isosceles triangle.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "I trimmed excess from the top or point end of the triangle and bent a right angle to fit under the light when it rests on my chest. I made another right angle bend where the sheet steel crests the top of the light. See the second photo. After you are finished, adjust the second bend as needed so the light points where you want it when in use and resting on your chest.",
